    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 29,
        "summary": "When the wicked rule, the people mourn\u2014The righteous consider the cause of the poor\u2014A fool speaks all that is in his mind\u2014Where there is no vision, the people perish.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "He, that being often reproved hardeneth his neck, shall suddenly be destroyed, and that without remedy.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 6:15.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 43
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When the righteous are in authority, the people rejoice: but when the wicked beareth rule, the people mourn.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Governments.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 5:4.",
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wickedness.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Authority; Leadership; Tyranny.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 89
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 7:23 (22\u201323); D&C 98:9.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso loveth wisdom rejoiceth his father: but he that keepeth company with harlots spendeth his substance.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Mosiah 11:4 (2\u20134).",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The king by judgment establisheth the land: but he that receiveth gifts overthroweth it.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A man that flattereth his neighbour spreadeth a net for his feet.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 46:5 (4\u201335).",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In the transgression of an evil man there is a snare: but the righteous doth sing and rejoice.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Transgress.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 12:6; D&C 10:26.",
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The righteous considereth the cause of the poor: but the wicked regardeth not to know it.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 86,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Scornful men bring a city into a snare: but wise men turn away wrath.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "If a wise man contendeth with a foolish man, whether he rage or laugh, there is no rest.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The bloodthirsty hate the upright: but the just seek his soul.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hel. 16:2; Ether 13:22 (13\u201315, 22).",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A fool uttereth all his mind: but a wise man keepeth it in till afterwards.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 63:64.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Mind.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 17:28 (27\u201328).",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "If a ruler hearken to lies, all his servants are wicked.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The poor and the deceitful man meet together: the Lord lighteneth both their eyes.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The king that faithfully judgeth the poor, his throne shall be established for ever.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kings, Earthly.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The rod and reproof give wisdom: but a child left to himself bringeth his mother to shame.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 13:24.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Chastening; Reproof.",
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Family, Children, Responsibilities toward.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Motherhood.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 80
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Shame.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When the wicked are multiplied, transgression increaseth: but the righteous shall see their fall.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Correct thy son, and he shall give thee rest; yea, he shall give delight unto thy soul.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 843
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Where there is no vision, the people perish: but he that keepeth the law, happy is he.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Revelation; Vision.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Individuals.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 43
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Luke 11:28.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:9.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Happiness.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 79
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "A servant will not be corrected by words: for though he understand he will not answer.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Seest thou a man that is hasty in his words? there is more hope of a fool than of him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Haste; Rashness.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 26:12.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that delicately bringeth up his servant from a child shall have him become his son at the length.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "An angry man stirreth up strife, and a furious man aboundeth in transgression.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Eccl. 7:9; Matt. 5:22.",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Strife.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A man's pride shall bring him low: but honour shall uphold the humble in spirit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 17:19; 18:12; Hel. 12:5 (1\u20135).",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Humility.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso is partner with a thief hateth his own soul: he heareth cursing, and bewrayeth it not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hate.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The fear of man bringeth a snare: but whoso putteth his trust in the Lord shall be safe.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "John 12:42 (42\u201343); 19:38. TG\u00a0Peer Influence.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Trust in God.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Many seek the ruler's favour; but every man's judgment cometh from the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 19:6.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "An unjust man is an abomination to the just: and he that is upright in the way is abomination to the wicked.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Ne. 15:36.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 59
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 79,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}